Friend function is not a member function of a class to which it is a friend.

Friend function is declared in the class with friend keyword.

It must be defined outside the class to which it is friend.

Friend function can access any member of the class to which it is friend.

Friend function can't access members of the class directly.

It has no caller object.

Pure Virtual Function or Abstract Function:

Implementation of all function cannot be provided in a parent class because we don't know the implmentation. such a class called as abstract class. 

A pure virtual function or abstract function in C++ is a virtual function for which we don't have implmentation, we only declare it. A pure virtual function is declared with 0 value in declaration.